According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Connected Home Devices Market was valued at USD 222 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 238 million in 2025 to USD 361 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.4% during the forecast period. The market is expanding steadily due to rising consumer demand for smart home automation, increasing adoption of AI-powered assistants, widespread deployment of high-speed internet and 5G networks, and growing investments in energy-efficient and connected living solutions.
Connected home devices—including smart lighting, security cameras, thermostats, voice assistants, and connected appliances—are transforming residential environments by enabling seamless automation, remote monitoring, and intelligent energy management. Advancements in artificial intelligence and machine learning are allowing devices to learn user preferences, automate daily routines, and deliver predictive home management capabilities. Strategic collaborations between device manufacturers, software providers, and utility companies are also simplifying installation and expanding smart home ecosystems, further driving market growth.
